WEBVTT

00:01.502 --> 00:05.547
♪ upbeat theme playing ♪

00:05.547 --> 00:08.926
<i>♪ Ba-ba-ba-ba,
ba-ba-ba-ba ♪</i>

00:08.926 --> 00:12.471
<i>♪ Ba-ba, da-da-da-da-da-da
da-da-da ♪</i>

00:15.682 --> 00:17.809
Son, sometimes in life,

00:17.809 --> 00:20.646
you have to perform a best friend rescue.

00:20.646 --> 00:23.857
Remember the time I had to drive you
to Aunt Val's house

00:23.857 --> 00:26.276
to stop her
from bleaching her hair?

00:26.276 --> 00:27.277
SOPHIE'S SON [on phone]:
<i>Yeah.</i>

00:27.277 --> 00:29.363
<i>I-I still don't really understand
what the big deal was.</i>

00:30.614 --> 00:32.658
How many times do I have to say it?

00:32.658 --> 00:35.035
<i>I'm</i> the blonde one!

00:35.035 --> 00:38.413
Okay. Swish and Val's
engagement party is tomorrow,

00:38.413 --> 00:41.500
and if we all work together,
we can make it a success.

00:42.125 --> 00:44.503
And here, we're defining success

00:44.503 --> 00:47.506
as killing this engagement dead.
Any questions?

00:48.048 --> 00:49.800
I'm straight off a plane here,

00:49.800 --> 00:51.844
so my question would be, what?

00:52.594 --> 00:54.805
A bubbly undergrad proposed to Val,

00:54.805 --> 00:56.265
and she doesn't wanna
go through with it,

00:56.265 --> 00:59.309
and I'm not ready
for married lame friends.

00:59.309 --> 01:00.352
[Sid clears throat]

01:01.520 --> 01:03.355
Except for you guys!

01:03.355 --> 01:05.107
Love your love.

01:05.732 --> 01:08.151
So, what am I looking at here, exactly?

01:08.151 --> 01:11.530
Um, well, I wanted to do a presentation,
but I ran out of time.

01:11.530 --> 01:12.948
Oh, so why'd you bring it?

01:12.948 --> 01:15.284
Well, I didn't buy PowerPoint
for nothing.

01:15.284 --> 01:17.119
Didn't you?

01:17.119 --> 01:18.412
Okay. Crazy thought.

01:18.412 --> 01:20.706
What if Val breaks up with Swish

01:20.706 --> 01:23.792
using words like, I don't know,
"I'm breaking up with you, Swish."

01:24.626 --> 01:26.670
Uh! We tried.

01:26.670 --> 01:30.591
Swish, you are a wonderful person,

01:30.591 --> 01:34.011
and I have so enjoyed
our time together.

01:34.011 --> 01:35.053
But...

01:37.097 --> 01:40.392
- You do it.
- I can't. I see it, too.

01:40.392 --> 01:41.643
♪

01:41.643 --> 01:44.479
Disappointing Swish face-to-face
is a no-go.

01:44.479 --> 01:47.858
So here's the plan.
Tomorrow, we are gonna convince Swish

01:47.858 --> 01:50.444
that he doesn't wanna marry Val. Ellen,

01:50.444 --> 01:53.155
you're gonna play
the role of "bitter divorced lady."

01:53.155 --> 01:56.658
Ooh! Can my name be Maureen?

01:56.658 --> 01:57.951
No. He's met you.

01:57.951 --> 01:59.411
Sid, Hannah.

01:59.411 --> 02:01.455
You guys are gonna be
the unhappy married couple

02:01.455 --> 02:02.956
who just can't stop fighting.

02:02.956 --> 02:05.209
This is our first weekend
together in a month,

02:05.209 --> 02:06.502
and we're supposed to fake a fight?

02:06.502 --> 02:08.795
Glad you get it. Charlie!

02:08.795 --> 02:12.090
You will be the fun bachelor
who's going to remind Swish

02:12.090 --> 02:13.800
of all the great casual sex

02:13.800 --> 02:15.844
he'll be missing out on
if he gets hitched.

02:15.844 --> 02:18.972
Love that for me, but I can't.
I'm bringing Julia.

02:18.972 --> 02:20.974
Oh, nice. How's that going, anyway?

02:20.974 --> 02:23.101
- Next topic, please.
- You don't like Julia?

02:23.101 --> 02:24.811
<i>Julia's</i> fine.

02:24.811 --> 02:27.689
Just having a little roommate kerfuffle.
It's nothing to fret over.

02:27.689 --> 02:29.233
Next. Topic. Please.

02:30.901 --> 02:33.987
Okay, Jesse, then you'll be
Mr. "I live for casual sex."

02:33.987 --> 02:35.989
[sighs] I hate guys like that.
What's your thing?

02:35.989 --> 02:37.699
- Can I just do that instead?
- No!

02:37.699 --> 02:40.786
<i>I</i> am gonna show Swish how ancient I am.

02:40.786 --> 02:43.163
Then, I'll mention that Val and I
are the same age,

02:43.163 --> 02:44.373
and he'll connect the dots.

02:44.373 --> 02:46.375
[gasps] Smart!
He loves Connect the Dots!

02:47.209 --> 02:48.627
Babe!

02:48.627 --> 02:51.129
It's not a horse!
It's a unicorn!

02:52.422 --> 02:53.757
I did that.

02:53.757 --> 02:55.259
Don't worry, Val.

02:55.259 --> 02:57.636
As soon as I'm done with you,
you are going to be...

02:57.636 --> 02:59.805
Single AF!

02:59.805 --> 03:02.224
That says "sing leaf."

03:03.183 --> 03:04.226
Damn it.

03:04.685 --> 03:07.354
I'm gonna be the most
married person in the world.

03:07.354 --> 03:10.941
♪

03:10.941 --> 03:12.943
So, um, if Swish asks,

03:12.943 --> 03:15.195
my parents are in India.

03:15.195 --> 03:16.572
What? Why?

03:16.572 --> 03:18.115
He wanted my dad's blessing,

03:18.115 --> 03:20.450
so I told him
they were out of the country.

03:20.450 --> 03:22.661
Photoshopped a picture of them
in front of the Taj Mahal.

03:23.245 --> 03:24.329
Fiancée!

03:24.329 --> 03:25.998
Hey... [nervous laugh]

03:26.957 --> 03:28.000
Mwah!

03:28.000 --> 03:29.209
Oh, my gosh.

03:29.209 --> 03:32.254
I just saw our unborn children
in your eyes.

03:32.254 --> 03:33.297
Do you see them in mine?

03:33.922 --> 03:36.175
Nope. Just, like,

03:36.175 --> 03:37.426
your pupils.

03:38.093 --> 03:40.637
Oh, right. I'm being stupid
because they say that you see

03:40.637 --> 03:43.140
the spark of the children
in the <i>mother's</i> eyes.

03:43.140 --> 03:45.184
You probably just see,
like, little sperms in mine.

03:45.184 --> 03:46.310
[nervous laugh]
[Sophie groans]

03:47.019 --> 03:48.312
[loud groan]

03:49.062 --> 03:50.814
Oh! Sorry.

03:51.315 --> 03:52.482
I guess it's true what they say.

03:52.482 --> 03:56.320
Back pain is youth just leaving the body.

03:56.320 --> 03:59.615
I'm going through changes now that
I'm creeping up on the big 3-1.

03:59.615 --> 04:01.491
You know what I realized the other day?

04:01.491 --> 04:03.577
When you're 31,

04:03.577 --> 04:05.412
Val's gonna be 43.

04:05.787 --> 04:07.080
[sexy purr]

04:08.248 --> 04:11.293
And when you're 43, she'll be 55.

04:11.293 --> 04:12.544
[sexy purr]

04:12.544 --> 04:14.546
We get it! You're a horny cat.

04:15.255 --> 04:17.758
I love being with an experienced woman.

04:17.758 --> 04:20.928
I think it's beautiful that you guys have
to take your pants off when you come home.

04:22.763 --> 04:24.014
[nervous laugh]

04:24.014 --> 04:25.432
Hey, have you met Jesse?

04:25.432 --> 04:27.768
[clears throat] Hey, hey, hey!

04:27.768 --> 04:30.395
So, tying the old knot, huh?

04:30.395 --> 04:31.688
Yeah. I could never.

04:31.688 --> 04:33.732
I'd get hung up thinking
about all those...

04:34.650 --> 04:37.069
tasty women I'd be missing out on.

04:37.819 --> 04:40.614
- Tasty--
- Tasty, tasty meat.

04:40.614 --> 04:42.908
Big ol' husks, huh? I mean,

04:42.908 --> 04:46.286
women are objects,
and the subject is sex,

04:46.286 --> 04:47.913
- am I right?
- Okay.

04:47.913 --> 04:50.415
Yeah, if you ask me, best to stay single

04:50.415 --> 04:53.418
'cause life's just
a big ol' bag of boobs.

04:55.254 --> 04:57.506
- What are you doing?
- Sorry.

04:57.506 --> 05:00.175
Was bag of boobs weird?
I was between that and butt parade.

05:01.343 --> 05:02.970
How did I ever have sex with you?

05:02.970 --> 05:04.221
Missionary, right?

05:06.557 --> 05:10.102
Marrying young was
the <i>biggest</i> mistake I've ever made.

05:10.102 --> 05:12.104
I'm a broken shell of a woman.

05:12.104 --> 05:15.524
Nothing like the <i>Maureen</i> I used to be.

05:16.024 --> 05:17.526
Wait, I thought your name was Ellen.

05:18.235 --> 05:20.904
You remember that?
God, you're a good listener.

05:21.280 --> 05:24.575
And plus, you don't <i>seem</i> broken.
Y-You have a cool job,

05:24.575 --> 05:28.036
you're a great friend, and Val says
your girlfriend is freakin' dope.

05:28.036 --> 05:29.496
Yeah, Rachel rules.

05:29.496 --> 05:31.915
I guess I'm kicking butt out there, huh?

05:31.915 --> 05:33.750
- Thanks, Swish.
- Hey, no problem, Maureen.

05:34.751 --> 05:36.628
Look, you wanna be called Maureen,
I'll call you Maureen.

05:37.421 --> 05:38.547
Later.

05:38.547 --> 05:40.132
[laughs, mutters]

05:41.508 --> 05:45.012
I'm sorry. He smiled at me,
and then I just forgot.

05:45.012 --> 05:47.598
A-And then, I had an overwhelming desire

05:47.598 --> 05:50.100
to-to be his mom,
but, like a chill one.

05:50.100 --> 05:52.311
Like, he could smoke in front of me.

05:53.061 --> 05:54.730
Mom?

05:54.730 --> 05:57.065
Ellen, that's it!

05:58.442 --> 06:00.694
You're pretty tough to talk
to sometimes, you know that?

06:01.320 --> 06:02.779
And then I'll say,

06:02.779 --> 06:05.490
"Church shmurch! Sunday's for football!"

06:05.490 --> 06:08.202
And then you'll say, "Well, I never."

06:08.202 --> 06:10.204
I've never once said that in my life.

06:10.204 --> 06:12.122
Okay, well,
do the other line we talked about.

06:13.207 --> 06:15.792
Fine. I'll say, "You're not gettin'
any of this tonight,"

06:15.792 --> 06:17.336
but I'm not pointing at my crotch.

06:18.170 --> 06:19.338
[phone dings]

06:19.338 --> 06:21.256
Wait, you have Zillow alerts on?

06:21.256 --> 06:22.966
Hell, yeah. Me, too.
[giggles]

06:22.966 --> 06:24.551
How do you feel about exposed brick?

06:24.551 --> 06:26.470
I know it makes me
a basic bitch, but I love it.

06:28.180 --> 06:30.682
Wait, Hannah,
this is for a house in Los Angeles.

06:31.725 --> 06:33.769
I live in a nice area.

06:33.769 --> 06:35.729
I got curious, that's all.

06:35.729 --> 06:38.398
Uh-huh. Curious like,

06:38.398 --> 06:40.817
"Look how much these suckers
paid for this dump,"

06:40.817 --> 06:43.445
or curious like, "I wanna be
one of these suckers"?

06:43.445 --> 06:45.447
What do you want me to say?

06:45.447 --> 06:49.243
I've lived in LA for a while now,
I love my job, I'm making friends...

06:49.243 --> 06:51.703
Yeah, Hannah, but we have a plan.
Like, you were supposed to move here

06:51.703 --> 06:52.955
when your residency is over.

06:52.955 --> 06:54.414
That's always been the plan.

06:54.414 --> 06:56.416
I don't wanna talk about this here.

06:56.416 --> 06:58.001
Can't we just fake fight now?

06:58.001 --> 07:01.129
We can't fake fight now.
We're in a real fight.

07:01.672 --> 07:02.923
♪

07:04.007 --> 07:05.300
Ellen, right?

07:05.300 --> 07:07.302
I'm Julia. I was actually at your place
the other night.

07:07.302 --> 07:09.680
Oh, I know you were. Hi.

07:10.514 --> 07:12.474
- You're looking well.
- As are you.

07:14.017 --> 07:16.103
- Why are you guys being weird?
- We're not.

07:16.103 --> 07:18.689
And there is no "we."
On your way now.

07:22.401 --> 07:24.111
Hey, babe. Long-ass pee, huh?

07:24.111 --> 07:25.737
What happened,
you drank too many Gatorades?

07:25.737 --> 07:27.739
Uh... sure.

07:27.739 --> 07:30.158
Oh, my boy Doink made it! <i>Doink!</i>

07:34.705 --> 07:38.000
Um, I gotta say, I'm not
feeling any <i>less</i> engaged.

07:38.000 --> 07:39.626
Okay, we've had some misses.

07:39.626 --> 07:41.837
Alright, but I have a new plan,
and the main thing

07:41.837 --> 07:44.173
that I want <i>you</i> to focus on

07:44.173 --> 07:47.926
is, is not being, um, mad at me.

07:47.926 --> 07:50.637
Hey.
We came as soon as we got your text.

07:50.637 --> 07:53.348
Oh, Val, what are we gonna do with you?

07:54.057 --> 07:56.059
♪

07:59.479 --> 08:02.149
You're engaged to a child?

08:02.149 --> 08:05.194
What have you done
to your life, my darling?

08:05.194 --> 08:07.487
It's because we gave her
that cell phone too early.

08:07.487 --> 08:09.573
That Motorola Razr rotted out her brain.

08:09.573 --> 08:12.492
- Oh...
- I need you guys to focus, okay?

08:12.492 --> 08:14.161
Swish wants your blessing,

08:14.161 --> 08:15.746
and if you don't give it to him,

08:15.746 --> 08:17.414
he will call it off.
For a guy named Swish,

08:17.414 --> 08:18.874
he's surprisingly traditional.

08:18.874 --> 08:21.376
You're engaged to someone named Swish?!

08:21.376 --> 08:23.837
- It's not his real name.
- What is?

08:27.466 --> 08:29.134
Okay, from <i>you</i>,

08:29.134 --> 08:32.012
I need disapproving dad. Glare at him.

08:32.012 --> 08:33.055
Can you glare for me, Juan?
JUAN: Yeah.

08:35.098 --> 08:36.350
[giggles]

08:36.350 --> 08:38.602
That's more of like a--
[laughs] a smolder.

08:38.602 --> 08:41.104
I-I'm sorry.
I have resting smolder face.

08:41.104 --> 08:43.482
- Oh, it's a curse...
- Oh, my God!

08:43.482 --> 08:44.733
How's this?

08:45.692 --> 08:47.903
Oh! There! That's the glare!

08:47.903 --> 08:50.906
And from you,
I want subtle disappointment.

08:50.906 --> 08:52.491
Gimme, like, a withering head shake.

08:53.659 --> 08:55.702
Less movement.
If it's slight, it hurts more.

08:57.412 --> 09:00.541
- Ooh, devastating.
- Mr. and Mrs. M?!

09:00.541 --> 09:03.043
Oh, my gosh, I'm so glad you guys made it!
I-I thought you were in India.

09:03.043 --> 09:06.046
Uh, th-they were! Uh, but India...

09:06.880 --> 09:09.633
- closed.
- [sighs] Damn, that sucks.

09:09.633 --> 09:12.636
- But welcome.
- He believes India closed?

09:13.720 --> 09:15.222
Uh, thank you.

09:15.222 --> 09:17.766
Hey, why don't you three
go get to know each other?

09:17.766 --> 09:18.767
Yeah! Yeah.

09:18.767 --> 09:20.185
Remember, glare and wither.

09:20.185 --> 09:23.021
And don't look directly into his eyes,
but don't get lost in his hair either.

09:25.232 --> 09:26.733
Hey, are you okay?

09:26.733 --> 09:28.735
I-I can tell something weird's
going on with you and Ellen.

09:29.319 --> 09:31.113
- It was an accident.
- What was?

09:31.113 --> 09:32.322
I've said too much.

09:32.322 --> 09:33.907
Never mind. You know,
I don't wanna know anymore.

09:33.907 --> 09:35.075
Fine, I'll tell you everything.

09:35.909 --> 09:37.911
<i>It was the first time
Julia had spent the night.</i>

09:39.288 --> 09:41.123
Your piggy got out of his pen...

09:41.123 --> 09:42.833
Wha?! What are you doing?! Whoa!
[Charles screaming]

09:43.417 --> 09:44.835
[Ellen yelps]

09:44.835 --> 09:46.587
Turns out,
Ellen and Julia are back twins.

09:46.587 --> 09:50.549
- I mean, I was destined to fail.
- She calls you "Piggy" in bed?

09:50.549 --> 09:51.884
What do you call her?

09:51.884 --> 09:53.635
"Farmer Julie."

09:53.635 --> 09:55.512
She's a dairy farmer
who dabbles in pork,

09:55.512 --> 09:57.556
and I'm a dainty little pig
who doesn't like the mud.

09:57.556 --> 09:59.558
You guys have been on,
like, three dates.

09:59.558 --> 10:01.018
Yes, I know.

10:01.018 --> 10:03.020
Still got a lot of world-building to do.

10:04.771 --> 10:06.773
I mean, what does LA have
that New York doesn't?

10:06.773 --> 10:09.401
LA has tons of great things.

10:09.401 --> 10:11.570
I live right near this <i>pupusa</i> place that--

10:11.570 --> 10:14.031
We have <i>pupusas!</i> You want <i>pupusas?</i>

10:14.031 --> 10:15.991
I'll get you a million <i>pupusas.</i>

10:15.991 --> 10:18.785
But they just don't taste as good here.
Maybe it's the water.

10:19.870 --> 10:22.414
No, no, no, no, no, no.
That is our thing, Hannah.

10:22.414 --> 10:24.875
New York is the one with the water.

10:26.376 --> 10:27.503
Sid,

10:27.503 --> 10:30.380
can we at least have a conversation
about you moving to LA.

10:30.380 --> 10:32.382
We're having it, Hannah!
It is not going well!

10:33.550 --> 10:34.801
Our plan was always--

10:34.801 --> 10:37.763
Yes, I know what the plan was,
but plans can change, Sid.

10:38.388 --> 10:41.683
Hey, guys? Uh, we're working
a parent angle right now,

10:41.683 --> 10:42.976
so I'll let you know if I need you.

10:43.727 --> 10:45.562
Loving this energy. It sounds

10:45.562 --> 10:48.232
<i>really</i> ugly in here. Thanks.

10:50.651 --> 10:52.653
I have some concerns.

10:52.653 --> 10:55.739
Valentina doesn't make much money,
and you're still in school.

10:56.490 --> 11:00.410
Yeah, you're right.
But that's why I whipped up this, uh,

11:00.410 --> 11:01.912
five-year financial plan.

11:01.912 --> 11:03.914
- Oh.
- Yeah.

11:03.914 --> 11:05.415
I would start night trucking after class.

11:05.415 --> 11:08.126
I-I have short sleeper syndrome,
so I only need about four hours.

11:08.126 --> 11:10.629
And if I work the Jersey-to-DC route
for the rest of college,

11:10.629 --> 11:13.215
I would be able to save up
for a sick-ass condo.

11:14.091 --> 11:15.926
Wow. You've really thought this through.

11:15.926 --> 11:18.262
Yeah, m-my buddy Doink is a econ major.

11:18.262 --> 11:19.346
<i>Doink!</i>

11:21.390 --> 11:23.767
O-Okay, okay, so you have a plan,

11:23.767 --> 11:25.769
but what is the rush to get married?

11:25.769 --> 11:27.312
I mean, you're just a kid.

11:27.312 --> 11:29.314
With mad due respect,

11:29.314 --> 11:31.483
I just love your daughter
way too much to wait.

11:32.109 --> 11:33.110
A-And plus,

11:33.110 --> 11:35.571
didn't Juan propose to you the day
that you guys graduated high school?

11:36.196 --> 11:37.197
He did.

11:37.197 --> 11:39.199
And it looks like it worked out
for you guys.

11:39.199 --> 11:40.951
[laughter]

11:40.951 --> 11:42.202
Why are they high-fiving?

11:42.744 --> 11:45.205
What the hell is he doing now?

11:45.205 --> 11:48.458
Oh God. It's happening to them.

11:49.126 --> 11:52.629
♪

11:56.341 --> 12:00.387
Okay. The bad news is
we gave Swish our blessing.

12:00.387 --> 12:02.973
But, the good news is...

12:02.973 --> 12:05.017
- You get to marry Swish.
- What?!

12:05.017 --> 12:07.769
No. She is <i>not</i> marrying Swish.

12:07.769 --> 12:08.979
Why not?

12:08.979 --> 12:11.481
You've never been with
anyone this wonderful.

12:11.481 --> 12:14.484
Are you sure that it gets better
than Swish, sweetheart?

12:14.484 --> 12:17.070
- Because we're not.
- That head of hair.

12:17.070 --> 12:18.322
Think of the grandchildren.

12:18.322 --> 12:20.699
This is crazy. This is insane.

12:20.699 --> 12:23.035
You guys, of course
it gets better than Swish.

12:23.035 --> 12:25.204
He's not even the full version
of himself yet!

12:25.204 --> 12:26.955
He still has three baby teeth.

12:27.664 --> 12:28.957
VALENTINA:
You know what?

12:29.958 --> 12:31.210
Um...

12:32.044 --> 12:33.045
Maybe they're right.

12:33.045 --> 12:34.546
What?

12:35.255 --> 12:38.425
I'll do it. I will marry Swish.

12:39.426 --> 12:40.427
[excited squeal]

12:41.553 --> 12:42.679
Just so you know...

12:43.305 --> 12:45.474
I haven't been this disappointed
in hot people

12:45.474 --> 12:48.977
since I saw Heidi Klum throw out a burger
just because it fell in a puddle.

12:51.438 --> 12:53.148
Okay.

12:53.148 --> 12:55.192
