how to fix your situation.

12:55.567 --> 12:58.612
- Charlie moves back to England.
- Unfair! You move back to England!

12:58.612 --> 12:59.905
Listen!

12:59.905 --> 13:03.367
What happened to you guys
reminded me of something.

13:03.367 --> 13:05.869
Something I've worked very hard to forget.

13:05.869 --> 13:06.662
♪

13:06.662 --> 13:09.164
<i>Back when I was with Meredith,
she stayed over all the time.</i>

13:09.164 --> 13:11.416
<i>I came home late one night,
heard the shower,</i>

13:11.416 --> 13:14.127
<i>figured Sid was asleep, so it must be her.</i>

13:14.127 --> 13:18.006
<i>Meanwhile, Sid was showering,
heard the door, assumed it was Hannah...</i>

13:18.006 --> 13:19.508
Okay, we see where this is going.

13:19.508 --> 13:21.510
So you saw your buddy naked. Big deal.

13:21.510 --> 13:24.388
That's not the issue.
It was what I heard.

13:24.388 --> 13:25.514
♪

13:25.514 --> 13:27.349
[Southern accent]
<i>Missin' some evidence, little lady?</i>

13:27.349 --> 13:29.351
[both yell]

13:30.269 --> 13:33.230
- Why was he Southern?
- Was his penis the evidence?

13:33.230 --> 13:34.565
Yes, Ellen.

13:34.565 --> 13:37.192
And I think he wanted her to...
tamper with it.

13:38.443 --> 13:40.195
Seeing your best friend in sex mode

13:40.195 --> 13:42.364
is one of the hardest things
in life to bounce back from.

13:42.364 --> 13:44.366
<i>The awkwardness is suffocating.</i>

13:44.366 --> 13:46.869
♪

13:46.869 --> 13:49.246
<i>And for Sid and I,
we thought it might be the end of us.</i>

13:50.873 --> 13:53.625
But then, one day, I was at a bookstore,

13:53.625 --> 13:55.961
<i>and I saw the answer
right there in front of me.</i>

13:55.961 --> 13:57.337
♪

13:57.337 --> 14:01.508
<i>Joe Pesci's 101 New York Musts.</i>

14:02.217 --> 14:05.387
Sid and I did every single
dumb activity in that book.

14:05.387 --> 14:08.182
And bit by bit, memory by memory,

14:08.182 --> 14:11.226
we buried the shower fiasco
deeper and deeper

14:11.226 --> 14:13.145
into the recesses of our minds,

14:13.145 --> 14:15.147
until we forgot about it entirely.

14:16.982 --> 14:17.983
Until now.

14:19.067 --> 14:20.569
We need that book.

14:20.569 --> 14:23.405
Charlie!
You've been ignoring me all night.

14:23.989 --> 14:25.991
Right. And that <i>will</i> stop...

14:26.950 --> 14:28.243
right after I go and do a series

14:28.243 --> 14:30.287
of Joe Pesci-approved activities
with my roommate.

14:30.287 --> 14:31.330
Okay.

14:33.040 --> 14:34.374
Alright, I'm out.

14:34.374 --> 14:37.294
Tell Charlie to find a new farmer.
He'll know what that means.

14:37.294 --> 14:39.796
Wait. Before you go...

14:40.797 --> 14:42.841
can I tell you about something
that happened to me?

14:44.593 --> 14:45.636
No.

14:49.139 --> 14:50.224
Hey.

14:50.224 --> 14:53.393
You can't seriously be
considering marrying Swish, right?

14:53.393 --> 14:54.978
You don't love him.

14:55.521 --> 14:59.191
No, I don't <i>love</i> him.
But, like, I love him!

14:59.191 --> 15:01.443
And my parents made some good points.

15:01.443 --> 15:03.946
He's an amazing man
that's obsessed with me.

15:03.946 --> 15:05.781
Why should I be running away from that?

15:05.781 --> 15:07.783
What about Charlie?

15:07.783 --> 15:09.785
Because I thought
that he was your endgame.

15:11.787 --> 15:14.248
So did I, but maybe I was wrong.

15:15.207 --> 15:17.334
Babe, come here!
I drew that bird that you dreamed about.

15:17.334 --> 15:18.460
Ooh!

15:25.008 --> 15:27.010
♪

15:28.512 --> 15:29.930
[sighs]

15:29.930 --> 15:31.098
SID:
Hey!

15:31.473 --> 15:32.891
What are you guys doing out here?

15:33.433 --> 15:35.435
Sophie put us on a timeout.

15:36.061 --> 15:38.939
I'm Sid, by the way.
Uh, we haven't really met,

15:38.939 --> 15:41.441
but Sophie has a picture
of you guys as her lock screen.

15:41.441 --> 15:42.651
That's troubling.

15:42.651 --> 15:46.071
Yeah. [laughs] I thought so, too. Um...

15:46.071 --> 15:48.657
Anyway, I heard you guys are,
like, the perfect couple,

15:48.657 --> 15:49.867
and I was just wondering

15:49.867 --> 15:52.494
if you guys could give me
some relationship advice.

15:52.494 --> 15:53.954
Of course.

15:54.496 --> 15:56.164
See, Babe? A podcast

15:56.164 --> 15:58.709
where we give relationship advice
to normals would kill.

15:58.709 --> 15:59.793
Ah...

16:01.086 --> 16:04.089
Have you guys ever wanted
totally opposite things,

16:04.089 --> 16:06.300
where only one of you could get your way?

16:06.300 --> 16:07.593
Yes.

16:07.593 --> 16:09.386
Years ago, I wanted to see
the Spider-Man

16:09.386 --> 16:10.762
where he's that little British boy.

16:11.430 --> 16:13.932
Juan wanted to see <i>Cats</i> instead,
so we did.

16:14.850 --> 16:15.851
Awful.

16:15.851 --> 16:17.853
I still carry guilt over that.

16:18.729 --> 16:20.189
Don't be too hard on yourself.

16:20.189 --> 16:22.482
The <i>Cats</i> you imagined was beautiful.

16:22.482 --> 16:24.484
- [laughs]
- Okay, yeah.

16:24.484 --> 16:26.737
You guys are probably not the people
to talk to about this.

16:26.737 --> 16:28.739
No, wait. Hey. Hold on. Um...

16:29.531 --> 16:31.241
There is one other thing.

16:32.576 --> 16:34.620
I always wanted to have more children,

16:34.620 --> 16:36.371
and she wanted just the one.

16:37.039 --> 16:40.834
That's a big one.
How'd you guys figure it out?

16:43.086 --> 16:45.088
Sometimes, there's no right answer.

16:46.131 --> 16:48.467
There's just your answer, or hers.

16:49.718 --> 16:51.178
I chose hers.

16:51.178 --> 16:54.348
♪

16:56.350 --> 16:58.352
Can I show you something I found?

16:58.852 --> 17:02.064
Sid, if this is another
hamster apology card,

17:02.064 --> 17:05.025
I will watch it and enjoy it,
but I will still be mad at you.

17:05.025 --> 17:07.444
[laughs] No, this is, uh,

17:07.444 --> 17:10.697
from the night we got engaged.
I never showed it to you.

17:13.700 --> 17:17.162
<i>Hey!
So, we just got back from the airport.</i>

17:17.162 --> 17:19.665
<i>Um, I wanted to document
this night together,</i>

17:19.665 --> 17:22.125
<i>but you had to go
be a badass surgeon.</i>

17:22.125 --> 17:24.753
<i>So, uh, it's just me now.</i>

17:25.170 --> 17:27.172
<i>Those people from the Uber
are still here!</i>

17:27.965 --> 17:30.008
<i>They seem fun. We're drinking.</i>

17:30.008 --> 17:33.262
<i>Also, you were totally right.
Jesse has a huge thing for the blonde.</i>

17:33.971 --> 17:34.972
[thud]

17:37.975 --> 17:40.727
[giggles, snorts]

17:40.727 --> 17:42.229
<i>Anyway, uh...</i>

17:42.229 --> 17:44.356
<i>Hey. I'm sad you had to go,</i>

17:44.356 --> 17:46.608
<i>but I really meant what I said earlier.</i>

17:46.608 --> 17:48.527
<i>Like, we can make it
through anything together.</i>

17:49.194 --> 17:50.529
<i>Whatever it takes.</i>

17:53.156 --> 17:56.451
It's time I started living up
to that promise again.

17:56.451 --> 17:59.955
So, Hannah, I am officially open to LA.

18:01.498 --> 18:03.876
Gonna try and imagine
what it's like to, you know,

18:04.585 --> 18:05.627
live there.

18:06.253 --> 18:08.005
- Really?
- Yeah.

18:08.005 --> 18:10.257
I mean, if you love it so much,
it's gotta be worth loving.

18:10.257 --> 18:11.258
[sighs]

18:13.886 --> 18:15.888
♪

18:15.888 --> 18:17.222
Mm... Yeah.

18:22.269 --> 18:23.312
[sighs]

18:24.855 --> 18:25.856
[sighs]

18:33.155 --> 18:34.907
Whatever this is, make it quick.

18:34.907 --> 18:37.159
Swish is on me about what
our wedding colors are gonna be.

18:37.159 --> 18:38.660
Okay, just gimme 30 seconds.

18:38.660 --> 18:40.120
♪

18:40.120 --> 18:42.039
- CHARLIE: <i>Mm.
- Okay, say something. I'm recording.</i>

18:42.039 --> 18:44.833
<i>Um, a huge congratulations</i>

18:44.833 --> 18:46.210
<i>to Hannah and Sid!</i>

18:46.210 --> 18:47.503
<i>It is Hannah and Sid, isn't it?</i>

18:47.503 --> 18:50.047
<i>I'm not sure, but you already said it,
so just push through.</i>

18:50.047 --> 18:52.132
<i>Um, well, we've only just met you,</i>

18:52.132 --> 18:55.010
<i>but we are truly very happy for you.</i>

18:55.010 --> 18:58.472
<i>You are clearly in love,
and I know how good that feels.</i>

18:58.972 --> 18:59.973
VALENTINA:
<i>Wait, what?</i>

18:59.973 --> 19:01.808
<i>You love me?</i>

19:01.808 --> 19:04.228
<i>No. No, I was
talking about somebody else.</i>

19:04.228 --> 19:06.230
<i>You don't actually know them.</i>
VALENTINA: <i>Oh, is that right?</i>

19:07.856 --> 19:09.066
<i>What about the video?</i>

19:09.066 --> 19:11.068
<i>Mm, who cares?
We're never gonna see it again.</i>

19:11.068 --> 19:13.070
<i>♪ Love, Try Not To Let Go</i>
by Julia Jacklin playing ♪

19:13.070 --> 19:15.155
Maybe you're right.

19:15.155 --> 19:17.866
Maybe Charlie is not your end game.

19:18.700 --> 19:21.245
But, for a while, you loved him, Val.

19:21.245 --> 19:23.747
You really, <i>really</i> loved him.

19:23.747 --> 19:26.041
And if you think that you can find
that kind of love

19:26.041 --> 19:28.544
with Swish, then I say go for it.

19:28.544 --> 19:30.045
But if you can't?

19:30.712 --> 19:33.715
Go find it. Okay?

19:33.715 --> 19:36.134
Whether that's with Charlie
or with someone else.

19:36.134 --> 19:39.638
<i>♪ Mmm, time ♪</i>

19:40.305 --> 19:41.807
No, you're right.

19:44.017 --> 19:46.019
I'll hold out for true love.

19:47.312 --> 19:48.981
God, thanks a lot, you asshole.

19:48.981 --> 19:50.858
[sniffles, sighs]

19:51.859 --> 19:54.069
<i>♪ Consumes the space between me ♪</i>

19:54.069 --> 19:56.864
She broke Swish's heart that night.

19:56.864 --> 19:59.867
<i>♪ And everyone I left ♪</i>

19:59.867 --> 20:03.328
<i>Oh, oh ♪</i>

20:03.328 --> 20:05.539
<i>♪ Love ♪</i>

20:07.416 --> 20:09.751
But he got happily married weeks later!

20:10.544 --> 20:11.753
He owns an island now.

20:13.881 --> 20:17.134
Didn't even have to pay for it.
The US government was just like,

20:17.134 --> 20:19.136
"Here!"

20:19.136 --> 20:21.638
Sorry. So sorry.

20:21.638 --> 20:22.931
Sorry.

20:24.349 --> 20:25.517
Look after him, Doink.

20:27.978 --> 20:29.771
We were trying to help.

20:29.771 --> 20:32.691
I know.
You want me to find true love,

20:32.691 --> 20:33.692
and I will.

20:33.692 --> 20:36.195
I wanted you to marry literally Swish.

20:38.071 --> 20:40.616
He'll get over it.
Just give him some time, huh?

20:43.160 --> 20:44.161
[scoffs]

20:44.703 --> 20:45.996
How do you feel?

20:47.080 --> 20:49.583
Guilty. Humiliated.

20:49.583 --> 20:50.542
And?

20:51.585 --> 20:53.212
BOTH: Single!

20:54.296 --> 20:55.214
We did it!

20:55.214 --> 20:58.091
♪

21:04.640 --> 21:07.100
We can look at each other
in the eye again. Watch.

21:08.018 --> 21:09.019
Huh?

21:09.019 --> 21:12.272
That book...
Jesse, why does that book look familiar?

21:13.273 --> 21:14.566
[gasps]

21:15.943 --> 21:17.819
Sid, we gotta go
to Times Square right now.

21:17.819 --> 21:18.487
Okay.

21:18.487 --> 21:20.155
♪

21:21.281 --> 21:24.284
♪
